##1
download Perl from https://www.activestate.com/activeperl/downloads
download active perl
download the windows version

##2
double click the downloaded file, install perl
select the "Typical" option

##3
after installation of perl, use cmd in windows and test the following command
perl -v

if the version information pop out, that means we have installed perl

##4
then we can execute the perl files in the eclipse

##5
sometimes in eclipse, when we execute the perl file , we lack of some packages, we can use the "perl package management" to install the related packages


